$10,000 or 18 years in jail.

478
00:41:28,491 --> 00:41:30,659
And 18 years in jail?!

479
00:42:27,049 --> 00:42:29,552
They're still talking.

480
00:42:31,554 --> 00:42:33,973
I'll stitch him up.

481
00:42:34,056 --> 00:42:36,225
No.

482
00:42:36,433 --> 00:42:38,394
It's OK, I'll do it.

483
00:42:59,415 --> 00:43:01,417
Good golly, Miss Molly

484
00:43:02,459 --> 00:43:05,129
Sure likes a ball

485
00:43:05,254 --> 00:43:08,174
When you're rockin' and a-rollin'

486
00:43:08,215 --> 00:43:10,759
Did you hear your momma call?

487
00:43:23,731 --> 00:43:25,691
All right!

488
00:43:25,816 --> 00:43:28,903
The town of Cicely wants
to welcome all of you

489
00:43:29,028 --> 00:43:35,409
to the ninth annual Arrowhead County
Summer Wonderland Festival.

490
00:43:37,786 --> 00:43:42,958
We'd especially like to welcome
our friends from Middlechurch,

491
00:43:43,042 --> 00:43:48,797
who came here to celebrate with us -
that's 300 miles away as the crow flies.

492
00:43:51,967 --> 00:43:54,678
Hello, Dr Fleischman.

493
00:43:54,845 --> 00:43:58,098
Mooseburger or caribou dog?

494
00:43:58,182 --> 00:44:00,017
Mooseburger.

495
00:44:00,100 --> 00:44:04,480
And I'm proud to be here
to celebrate that fact!

496
00:44:04,605 --> 00:44:10,611
You all have a really good time. Sit back,
enjoy the food, drink and fellowship,

497
00:44:10,736 --> 00:44:14,406
and have a hell of a good time!

498
00:44:14,490 --> 00:44:17,159
North to the future!

499
00:44:28,379 --> 00:44:31,423
What time is it in New York City now?

500
00:44:32,883 --> 00:44:34,927
It's around midnight.

501
00:44:36,178 --> 00:44:41,517
So I guess maybe you and your fiancée'd
be coming back from a movie about now.

502
00:44:41,559 --> 00:44:46,021
Maybe stop by a little café
for a cup of espresso,

503
00:44:46,188 --> 00:44:49,275
pick up the Sunday edition
of the New York Times,

504
00:44:49,358 --> 00:44:53,863
and some fresh, hot bagels
for breakfast tomorrow.

505
00:44:54,029 --> 00:44:56,031
Sounds about right.

506
00:44:57,032 --> 00:44:59,368
How do you know about bagels?

507
00:44:59,410 --> 00:45:03,414
Oh, I saw Manhattan.
I think Woody's a genius.

508
00:45:11,255 --> 00:45:13,340
Maurice?

509
00:45:27,354 --> 00:45:30,566
I got nothin' to say to you, Maurice.

510
00:45:31,484 --> 00:45:34,528
But I'm sayin' it anyway.

511
00:45:38,532 --> 00:45:40,534
How's she doin'?

512
00:45:42,369 --> 00:45:44,413
She's fine.

513
00:45:47,750 --> 00:45:51,587
I miss you, Maurice.
I miss you bein' around.

514
00:45:53,422 --> 00:45:56,717
Things kinda got turned upside-down.

515
00:45:58,260 --> 00:46:00,304
Gravity.

516
00:46:02,306 --> 00:46:05,434
It keeps you rooted to the ground.

517
00:46:07,311 --> 00:46:10,606
In space, there's not any gravity.

518
00:46:10,648 --> 00:46:15,611
You just kind of leave your feet
and go floatin' around.

519
00:46:18,656 --> 00:46:21,492
Is that what it's like, Holling?

520
00:46:22,660 --> 00:46:24,870
What?

521
00:46:24,995 --> 00:46:26,997
Bein' in love.

522
00:46:44,598 --> 00:46:47,309
How do you like the mooseburger?

523
00:46:47,434 --> 00:46:51,313
- Little gamy.
- Well, you'll get used to it.

524
00:46:52,273 --> 00:46:55,776
The dream is gone I thought was mine

525
00:46:55,943 --> 00:46:59,363
There's nothing left for me to do

526
00:46:59,488 --> 00:47:05,619
But cry over you

527
00:47:05,703 --> 00:47:09,957
Well, I never felt
more like singin' the blues

528
00:47:10,040 --> 00:47:13,294
Cos I never thought that I'd ever lose

529
00:47:13,419 --> 00:47:15,754
Your love, dear

530
00:47:15,880 --> 00:47:21,177
You got me singin' the blues



